covidLtcNotes.notes:
Nevada reports long-term care data for both Skilled Nursing Facilities and Assisted Living Facilities. Data is separated by resident and staff cases and deaths. Nevada reports cumulative data of reported outbreaks. The state defines an outbreak as a facility that has two or more laboratory confirmed COVID-19 positive cases of clients, or two or more laboratory confirmed COVID-19 cases of someone linked to a facility. Nevada includes data on “Imported” cases - residents who were confirmed positive prior to entering a facility. 

February 4, 2021: Cumulative nursing home resident cases decreased by 15.

February 18, 2020: Nursing Home cumulative resident deaths dropped from 503 to 492 and Assisted Living cumulative facilities impacted dropped from 153 to 151. 

March 4, 2021: Nevada's assisted living staff positives decreased by 1.
